    "Evaluating responsible use and mitigating potential negative applications becomes imperative [2,[7][8][9].",
    "Addressing Bias and Stereotypes One prominent concern surrounding language models is their susceptibility to inheriting and magnifying biases present in their extensive training datasets [66,67].",
    "These datasets, comprising vast amounts of real-world text and code, often contain societal prejudices and historical inequalities.",
    "For example, if a dataset links certain job titles more frequently with a specific gender, the language model may reflect this bias in its outputs.",
    "To counteract these biases, strategies such as diversifying training data, filtering out harmful content, and incorporating debiasing techniques during model training are essential."
